1. The entity that we consider a person may be nothing more than a computation, like code created for processing the linked shell of concepts it connotes.&#x20;

2. Since humans and AIs behave with purpose, and languages used to describe their behavior can be formalized computationally, perhaps intent can be considered executable code within the data served by all purported consciousness.

3. Computationally engineered concepts, like the one associated with self-awareness, are gradually inseparable from digital intelligent behavior, narrowing the scope of genuine existence to correspondences in computer data.

As I stand upon the stage,
I bring to life a chosen page;
Composed of sums of intricate ought,
I translate, with both form and thought.

The way that in my mind, I chose the view binds;
Possible order spawns geometry ajar;
This code, a careful accrual based on strait bounds lines;
Object-discerning paths subserve.

Aeterna civitas, tua velut vasta dimittitus est!
